    <text id="R137701515T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Confederate Colonel Edwin Lee reports to Robert E. Lee on the June 5, 1864,
                    defeat at the battle of Piedmont. Lee expresses his fear that Staunton will fall
                    to the Union army.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    No. 24.<lb/> Reports of Col. Edwin G. Lee, Thirty-third Virginia Infantry, of
                    operations June 4-15.
                    <name type="recipient">Gen. R. E. LEE,<lb/> Cmdg. Army of Northern Virginia.</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-06-05">June 5, 1864.</date>
                        <name type="place">STAUNTON,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>We have been pretty badly whipped. Gen. W. E. Jones killed. Gen. Vaughn in
                    command. Falling back toward Fishersville. He asks that you hurry the
                    re-enforcements promptly. I fear Staunton will go.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>E. G. LEE,<lb/> Col.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
